questiontext.text:
Given the following two functions,

\(f(x)={@fx@}\)
\(g(x)={@gx@}\)

Determine the composition \(f(g(x))\).

generalfeedback.text:
Worked Solution

To find \(f(g(x))\) we need to apply the function \(f(x)\) to the function \(g(x)\). We compute the following,

\(\begin{align*} f(g(x)) &= f({@gx@}) \\ &= {@aa*(x^2+cc)+bb@} \\ &= {@ta1@} \end{align*}\)
